tation Notes\n    44→\n    45→- Import `resolve_instance`, `load_config` from `instance_paths`\n    46→- For `--all`, glob `orch_dir / \"instances\" / \"*\" / \"state.json\"` — skip dirs with no state.json\n    47→- One-line summary format suggestion: `M8  |  Phase: Foundation  |  Wave: 3  |  Tickets: 12/28 done`\n    48→\n    49→---\n    50→\n    51→## Handoff Notes\n    52→\n    53→(Leave blank until handoff occurs.)\n    54→\n    55→---\n    56→\n    57→## Activity Log\n    58→\n    59→- 2026-03-01 [producer] Created — T4 Foundation phase\n    60→- 2026-03-01 [systems-programmer] Starting work — updating status.py with --instance and --all flags\n    61→- 2026-03-01 [systems-programmer] DONE — committed 8c7b730, merged PR https://github.com/sqlhammer/Hammer-Forge-Studio/pull/218\n    62→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"36142e0f-0ce3-4c03-9bff-d9ba36b531fa","uuid":"8d67e184-12a4-475f-abb8-3864f4dbf336","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\tickets\\T4\\TICKET-0251.md","content":"---\nid: TICKET-0251\ntitle: \"Update status.py for --instance and --all flags\"\ntype: FEATURE\nstatus: DONE\npriority: P1\nowner: systems-programmer\ncreated_by: producer\ncreated_at: 2026-03-01\nupdated_at: 2026-03-01\nmilestone: \"T4\"\nphase: \"Foundation\"\ndepends_on: [\"TICKET-0249\"]\nblocks: [\"TICKET-0256\"]\ntags: [orchestrator, status, instance-paths, t4-foundation]\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nUpdate `orchestrator/status.py` to support `--instance <name>` (target a specific instance),\n`--all` (list all instances with a one-line summary each), and auto-detection (when only one\ninstance exists, use it without requiring `--instance`).\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [x] `--instance <name>` argument added (optional)\n- [x] `--all` flag added: iterates `orchestrator/instances/*/state.json`, prints a one-line\n  summary per instance (instance name, milestone, phase, current wave, ticket counts)\n- [x] Auto-detect logic:\n  - If `--all` passed: show all instances\n  - If `--instance` passed: show that instance\n  - If neither and exactly one instance dir exists: use it automatically\n  - If neither and multiple instance dirs exist: print a helpful message listing instances and\n    ask user to specify `--instance <name>` or `--all`\n  - If neither and no instance dirs exist: print \"No instances found. Run start_milestone.py first.\"\n- [x] `resolve_instance()` used for all path resolution (replaces any hardcoded flat paths)\n- [x] Existing status display output format preserved for single-instance view\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Import `resolve_instance`, `load_config` from `instance_paths`\n- For `--all`, glob `orch_dir / \"instances\" / \"*\" / \"state.json\"` — skip dirs with no state.json\n- One-line summary format suggestion: `M8  |  Phase: Foundation  |  Wave: 3  |  Tickets: 12/28 done`\n\n---\n\n## Handoff Notes\n\n(Leave blank until handoff occurs.)\n\n---\n\n## Activity Log\n\n- 2026-03-01 [producer] Created — T4 Foundation phase\n- 2026-03-01 [systems-programmer] Starting work — updating status.py with --instance and --all flags\n- 2026-03-01 [systems-programmer] DONE — committed 8c7b730, merged PR https://github.com/sqlhammer/Hammer-Forge-Studio/pull/218\n","numLines":62,"startLine":1,"totalLines":62}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CGD87p1Ayn5ByiV44dr3MN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"TICKET-0251 covers `status.py` updates for `--instance` and `--all` flags. The acceptance criteria for TICKET-0251 include `load_config` import, but don't explicitly say \"show config values\". The note \"Import `resolve_instance`, `load_config` from `instance_paths`\" is in the Implementation Notes, but the acceptance criteria don't require `status.py` to display config.\n\nThe gap between what TICKET-0256's acceptance criteria specifies (\"`status.py --instance M8` shows `session_ceiling_usd: 10`\") and what was implemented (no config display in `status.py`) means the QA acceptance criterion cannot be verified as specified.\n \nThe config layering mechanism itself works when called directly in Python, but `status.py` never got the feature to actually display those config values—it wasn't part of TICKET-0251's acceptance criteria. This means I need to log this as a failing criterion and create a bug ticket to address the missing functionality.\n\nLooking at the ticket numbering, the next available number would be TICKET-0257. But before I file it, I should clarify whether this is truly a missing feature or if the test criterion in TICKET-0256 was asking for something that was never supposed to be implemented in the first place.\n\nAs QA, my job is to test against the stated criteria—if the test says `status.py` should display config values and it doesn't, that's a failure worth reporting. The systems-programmer who owns status.py would need to address it.\n\nChecking the implementation notes from TICKET-0251, there's a mention of importing `load_config` from `instance_paths`, but looking at the actual status.py code, only `resolve_instance` is imported. The `load_config` function was never brought in, which explains why config values aren't being displayed.\n\nThis is a legitimate gap I should file as a P2 bug—the feature was specified but not fully implemented. The systems-programmer owns the fix since they maintain status.py. I'll assign it TICKET-0257 based on the sequence. Now I need to clean up the test instances I created since they were only for validation purposes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"sto